Author: Karen Kasler
Content: Also: @TargetSmart says the numbers of first-time voters in all age groups voting early were up 125.89% nationally compared to 2014, and up 104.24% in Ohio. The numbers of “super voters” (who almost always vote) are up 42.95% nationally, and 23.82% in Ohio.

Author: Karen Kasler
Content: Provisional ballots are required to ensure that a voter's eligibility is verified. I assume the provisional ballot is required for those who requested absentee ballots to ensure that the absentee ballot wasn't already cast. And typically more than 80% of provisionals are counted.

Author: Karen Kasler
Content: That's in line with a prediction from @midawson, who said he thought there won't be a "blue wave" but perhaps "blue tornadoes" in Ohio House districts that voted for Clinton in 2016: http://www.statenews.org/post/experts-try-predict-if-early-turnout-shows-whether-red-tide-or-blue-wave-building-ohio …https://twitter.com/kkondik/status/1059496107544317955 …

Author: Karen Kasler
Content: OH early vote 2018: 1,491,762 absentee ballots requested,1,313,844 cast. In the midterms in 2014, 813,106 absentee ballots were cast - but turnout was only 40.53%. In the 2016 presidential election, when 71.33% turned out in Ohio, 1,798,277 absentee ballots were cast. #OHVote18

Content:
En kronisk sykdom er en sykdom du må regne med å ha resten av livet, selv om du ikke er født med den.

På samme måte må det å være kronisk norsk bety at du har tenkt å være norsk resten av livet, selv om du ikke er født her i landet.

Author: Dr. Dave Stukus
Content:
Great question! There are exactly zero validated tests to diagnose food sensitivity. 

This includes:
Mediator release test
IgG testing
Applied kinesiology
Hair analysis
Neutralization provocation

There is no evidence, and in most cases a plausible mechanism, to support these https://twitter.com/ArmedSC/status/1061127435633090561 …

Content:
IgG testing. It’s a ‘proper’ test.
